.TH "stm32_timers_dma_burst_read" 9 "stm32_timers_dma_burst_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stm32_timers_dma_burst_read \- Read from timers registers using DMA.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" stm32_timers_dma_burst_read
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 *buf "  ","
.BI "enum stm32_timers_dmas id "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int bursts "  ","
.BI "unsigned long tmo_ms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
reference to stm32_timers MFD device
.IP "buf" 12
DMA'able destination buffer
.IP "id" 12
stm32_timers_dmas event identifier (ch[1..4], up, trig or com)
.IP "reg" 12
registers start offset for DMA to read from (like CCRx for capture)
.IP "num_reg" 12
number of registers to read upon each DMA request, starting \fIreg\fP.
.IP "bursts" 12
number of bursts to read (e.g. like two for pwm period capture)
.IP "tmo_ms" 12
timeout (milliseconds)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Read from STM32 timers registers using DMA on a single event.
